# Ponas Obuolys Project Rules

## Language Requirements
- All code, comments, and documentation must be in Lithuanian, except for technical terms and variable names
- Use proper Lithuanian grammar and spelling in all user-facing content
- Maintain consistent terminology across the project

## Code Style
- Follow the React TypeScript style guide
- Use camelCase for variables and functions
- Use PascalCase for components and interfaces
- Use kebab-case for file names
- Maximum line length: 100 characters
- Use 2 spaces for indentation
- Always use semicolons
- Use single quotes for strings
- Always use explicit type annotations

## Project Constraints
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Support for modern browsers only (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)
- Accessibility compliance (WCAG 2.1 AA)
- Performance optimization for fast loading times
- SEO-friendly content structure
- Secure coding practices
